defaultIn the long run, when you look at what is happening now with the budget cuts in local authorities, if we start imposing barriers, whereby every single local contracting authority starts to favour, in one way or another, their local supplier base, what will happen is that no
default-
defaultone is going to grow, because even if they get 100% of that local pie, two years or five years down the line the local pie is going to shrink and they will not be able to win business elsewhere.
