default 
defaultThe effect of driving down the price and disadvantaging small businesses in their own area is only depressing growth within their own area, as well, which they then have to counteract by spending more money.
default 
defaultIt is perfectly rational not to advantage small businesses, but to take away unnecessary barriers.
defaultThere were four fairly simple recommendations that came out of our own research.
default 
defaultYou simplify the PQQ process and make it much more straightforward and standardised.
default 
defaultYou break down major contracts into lots.
default 
defaultYou have to go out there and try to engage with the small
default-
defaultbusiness community.
default 
defaultWe found that something like 70% of small businesses were not interested in engaging with local councils.
default 
defaultIn fact, it was easier to get them to export than to get them to trade with their local councils.
default 
defaultYou have to go out and actively engage with them.
default 
defaultThe final thing, which is a big incentive, is you say, “If you are going to get paid quickly, pass that on.”
default 
defaultMany councils do pay very quickly to their tier
default-
defaultone, prime contractors.
default 
defaultWith 
defaultWakefield
default, we saw that it was very 
defaulteasy to include a contract term that meant they had to pass on those quite swift payment terms to their tier
default-
defaulttwo and tier
default-
defaultthree suppliers.
default 
defaultThat has a dramatic effect on take
default-
defaultup within the community.
defaultQ365 default&#xa0; 
