defaultHowever, we have not had opportunities come from it.
default 
defaultYou can further add that each local council has a different portal for its own procurement.
default 
defaultYou try to be a part of each of these, because it is important.
default 
defaultIn the end, the question to you would be, “How many framework agreements and portals does a company need to be a part of for the same requirement to be able to get business?”
default 
defaultIt takes a lot of time and money to manage these kinds of things.
defaultAll in all, we have not seen the framework and collaboration side of things as being that beneficial, unfortunately.
default 
defaultG
default-
defaultCloud and the Dynamic
default 
defaulteMarketplace
default are a step in the right direction, but you need a bit more common sense applied to that.
default 
defaultThe SMEs can offer a lot of innovation, which is really important.
defaultDr defaultTellesdefault:default Building upon that, if you look at collaboration by itself it means, as you are probably implying, you are going to have less contracts available and the contracts are going to be bigger.
default 
defaultThe bigger a contract is, the more difficult it is for an SME or a micro-company to win that business.
default 
defaultThat is clear.
default 
defaultThat is one way of looking at things.
defaultThe other way to look at it is if you have collaboration of councils and a little bit more centralisation, you are going to have procurers who are going to be more expert.
default 
defaultYou are going to have people who are going to be more trained and more able to deliver good procurement.
default 
defaultIf you use that work, especially with the use of e-procurement, and you start to advertise lower
default-
defaultvalue contracts, which currently are not being advertised across the 
defaultUK
default, you open a huge number of opportunities for SMEs to bid directly for those contracts.
defaultFor example, look at the data published by the European
default 
defaultCommission regarding 2010
default&#x2011;
default11.
default 
defaultIn the 
defaultUK
default, only 25% of contracts are above the EU thresholds.
default 
defaultThe other 75% have a value that is below the thresholds.
default 
defaultBelow the threshold, pretty much every contracting authority can do what they want, obviously with the caveat that now Government Departments and Ministries are forced or supposed to advertise contracts above £10,000.
default 
defaultOther than that, any other contracting local authority may do what they want.
default 
defaultIf they pool those resources together and start to advertise those contracts, in the end you may have more contracts altogether being advertised that are more attuned to the needs of SMEs.
defaultQ366 default&#xa0; 
defaultJohn Stevenson:default The skills, expertise and the experience of councils and their council officers clearly matters.
default 
defaultHow do you rate the ability of councils to deal with small suppliers and small businesses and their capacity?
defaultMartin defaultMcTaguedefault: What we found was that it was generally pretty good—surprisingly good.
default 
defaultThere were more examples of good practice than bad.
default 
defaultHowever, there was nobody doing everything they could do.
default 
defaultFor example, with splitting into lots, only 39% of councils had actively participated in splitting down major contracts into lots, which is quite poor.
default 
defaultSpreading that good practice would be relatively easy.
defaultHowever, the biggest factor we saw—I know other witnesses to the Committee have said the same thing—is this risk aversion, which seems to stifle a lot of what goes on in this area.
default 
defaultIt is not like these guys do not know what to do.
default 
defaultIt is that, in this very tense environment of local
default 
defaultgovernment at the moment, they are more frightened of losing their job.
default 
defaultSometimes, the responsibility for that situation may fall on members.
default 
defaultMembers have to say, “We are going to back the officers to be more innovative, to take a few more risks and take the opportunity to engage with small business”, because that will carry a bit more risk, but it carries a lot more benefits.
defaultQ367 default&#xa0; 
defaultJohn Stevenson:default Does your own organisation have a role to play in this?
defaultMartin defaultMcTaguedefault: Yes, we do.
defaultQ368 default&#xa0; 
